 and actual nutrient content on the plots within these union-councils.
 More could be done by exploiting the geo-location capabilities of digital
 decision support tools.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Another problem is that some applications focus on maximizing yields and
 to not consider costs.
 However, optimal fertilizer application is likely to change with both input
 and output prices.
 Again, the extent to which this can be integrated into an application can
 vary.
 The CABI app for instance, does consider the cost of inputs when optimizing
 fertilizer allocation but farmers have to input the prices of the fertilizers.
 A better way would be to link the application to prices that get updated
 in real-time.
\end_layout

